ABUJA – The Special Assistant to FCT Minister on Youths, Commandant Isaac David, has urged youths in the Federal Capital Territory (FCT), to see themselves as leaders and refuse to be used as touts and thugs by politicians before,during and after the forthcoming Area Councils election in the nation’s capital. Addressing journalists after he was briefed by some aggrieved youths on the clash between some youths supporters of contestants of the Bwari Area Council Chairmanship seat, he disclosed that politicians are in the habit of giving youths money to engage in the destruction of lives and property, but are only concerned about destroying the future of the youths. David who is also an indigenous youths leader in the FCT, said youths are leaders of today and tomorrow, and great leaders of today achieve their greatness from their youthful age and do not allow themselves to be used as political thugs. Abia Chief Judge Releases 14 Prison Inmates I Can’t Afford Lawyer, Autopsy, But I Want Justice For My… He advised youths to engage political contestants on lingering issues that concern the youths, especially appointingSpecialAssistant of Youth Matters in each of their councils if voted into the office, adding that youths of today do not have any reason not to do better. He urged FCT youths in every Area Council of the territory to wake up and take his place in every aspect of the leadership to provide innovative ideas for breakthrough and development that would make Abuja and its Councils stand shoulder to shoulder with other developed states in the country and the continent. He said, “The solution to the problem of FCT lies in the inner abilities of the FCT youths. Some politicians trusted by our youths have failed to inspire, motivate, mentor and empower the youths to live their inner abilities for the growth and advancement in the territory.